<paragraph blockId="7.[151,750,151,213]" box="[151,280,187,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,272,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Figs 4a–g</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="438" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuznetsov et Ren" authorityName="Kuznetsov et Ren" box="[559,888,259,286]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apioides">
<emphasis box="[559,684,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">A. apioides</emphasis>
Kuznetsov et Ren
</taxonomicName>
in external appearance but can be separated from the latter by the much larger body size and the pointed apex of penis (
<figureCitation box="[932,1014,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="438" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[402,568,331,358]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="1.98" metricValueMin="1.92" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" unit="mm" value="1.95" valueMax="1.98" valueMin="1.92">1.92–1.98 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[638,804,331,358]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.48" metricValueMin="1.42" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.48" valueMin="1.42">1.42–1.48 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[869,1034,331,358]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.549999999999999" metricValueMax="9.7" metricValueMin="9.399999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" unit="mm" value="0.955" valueMax="0.97" valueMin="0.94">0.94–0.97 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.33–1.36, EL/EW: 1.08– 1.10, PL/PW: 0.50–0.51, HW/PW: 0.65–0.67, PW/EW: 0.65–0.66.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
Body oval, moderately convex, dorsum with pale yellow pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[992,1107,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Figs 4a–c</figureCitation>
). Head, antennae and mouthparts yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[426,511,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
), tip of mandibles dark brown. Pronotum and scutellar shield yellowish brown. Elytra yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[429,543,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Figs 4a–c</figureCitation>
). Underside yellowish brown. Legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
Head with fine frontal punctures, slightly larger than eye facets, 1.0–2.0 diameters apart. Eye densely faceted, interocular distance 0.4 times of head width (
<figureCitation box="[651,732,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
). Pronotal punctures slightly larger than those on frons, 1.0–2.0 diameters apart. Surface of elytra with punctures much larger than those on pronotum, separated by 0.5–3.0 diameters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
Abdominal postcoxal lines complete and slightly recurved, reaching about 1/2 length of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
), area enclosed by the lines finely and sparsely punctate, irregularly distributed, broadly smooth along the lines; ventrite 1 with fine and sparse punctures at middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
Male genitalia. Penis slender, slightly broadened at base, apex pointed (
<figureCitation box="[993,1074,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
); tegminal strut stout with membranous appendages on both sides (
<figureCitation box="[547,631,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[600,631,799,825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" unit="g" value="4.0">4g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); tegmen with penis guide slightly shorter than 1/2 length of parameres, in lateral view widest at base, gradually tapering to apex (
<figureCitation box="[788,866,835,862]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4f</figureCitation>
); in inner view, penis guide stout and subtriangular, widest at base, gradually narrowing to apex (
<figureCitation box="[657,740,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[709,740,871,897]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" unit="g" value="4.0">4g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); parameres clavate and elongate with few setae at apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651167/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Figs 4f–g</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
